DAY v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [H. C. No. 23,

September Term, 1958.]

Decided October 23, 1958.

Before Bruñe, C. J., and Henderson, Hammond, Prescott and Horney, JJ.

PER Curiam.

The application for leave to appeal from the denial of a writ of habeas corpus is denied for the reasons set out in the opinion of the court below.
